Lockdown of East Ghouta, Syria for the past 4 years has left 400K people cut off from a regular supply of food, medicines &amp; other essentials.

@WFP needs more funding &amp; greater access to provide the help families need.
https://t.co/vzYCE0cuSb

Preparing a hot meal can be a challenge for Rohingya refugees as  they have to venture into unsafe areas to collect firewood. 

@WFP's fuel-efficient stoves are reducing risks &amp; providing clean energy. 

https://t.co/P7ykV8IT4a
